Caption:
Dolls, letâ€™s talk beauty! I want to talk about the @farsalicare Unicorn Essence which has officially become my beauty must-have. I have a normal skin type, but I have noticed patches & with this serum, my foundation is even and smooth. Now the @sephoracollection Sephora PRO Warm Palette - I used the colors "Ochre - Brass -Sepia". The pigments are amazing and the color choices are even better. The @theouai Wave Spray was quite interesting for me as a hair enthusiast. YES, I recommend using the spray & using pin-curls for a lovely volumized "oldies" look. The spray gives A LOT of texture!! For this look, I wanted to do soft, small waves, but I am looking forward to doing an IG live on the oldies hair look! What do you all think? 
I got all of these products at Sephora inside @JCPenney #SephoraInJCP #ad

LABEL: Post
Caption:
This past week the hubby and I had the pleasure to visit one of our favorite places in the Los Angeles-Southern California area, @unistudios . .
.
Over the years, he and I have visited Universal Studios many times individually and together we have been 3 times now. .
.
Some of the favorite features have been there for years and some, are fairly new. There is always something new to experience making the visit always worth it. .
.

Our visit this time was well timed with the Chinese Lunar New Year. Universal Studios is well decorated for this holiday with a full courtyard decked out in traditional red colors, including Lanterns, Pink Cherry Blossom trees which included wish/prayer cards you could attach to the tree. A live stage show for the family discussing ancient Chinese stories read out loud by costumed actors and involving audience members with props to make it a fun show for the whole family.
.
.

In addition to the Lunar New Year celebrations, the park is full of dozens of attraction and rides including the new The Wizarding World of Harry Potter. Watch my feed over the next several days to see a separate post exclusively about that. .

The tour is as fun as ever, with the usual back lot tram tour. Then there were the rides! I have yet to experience a ride that is not a ton of fun. In fact, some of the rides were so thrilling that they had me pretty scared..lol. .
.The shows such as the Special Effects, Water World, Kung Fu Panda & the Scary Walking dead all were worth doing all over again. So much so, that we are already talking about when to go back again.
.
.

As I said, stay tuned for my special post about The Wizarding World of Harry Potter. As this was all new to me and there was so much to see and experience, I am doing a full separate post just about that part of the park! .
.
If you have been to Universal Studios Hollywood, I would love to hear what you thought. What was your favorite part of the park? .
.
